    <body>
      <head>Wolf Dietrich Oppel</head>
      <div>

        <p>Adopted son of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard Oppel</ref> and his first wife, <ref
            cRef="entity-008528">Käthe Oppel (<hi rend="italic">née</hi> Brebeck)</ref>; second
          child of <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard Oppel</ref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p>Presumably when <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-008528"
            >Käthe</ref> divorced in 1910 Wolf and his older sister, <ref cRef="entity-008525"
            >Ingeborg Maria Oppel</ref>, were assigned to the custody of their mother. Wolf features
          in the correspondence between <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard</ref> and Heinrich
          Schenker only once: “Wolf wants to go to America” (<ref type="correspondence"
            cRef="OJ-13-10_149b">OJ 13/10, [149b]</ref>); and in that between <ref
            cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette
            Schenker</ref> after Heinrich’s death in 1935: “Wolf has been transferred to Berlin”
            (<ref type="correspondence" cRef="OJ-13-10_192">OJ 13/10, [192]</ref>, March 3, 1935).
          Nothing more is known of him.</p>
      </div>

    </body>

